title: A new song of Moggie's jealousie: or Jockies vindication Moggy from Jockey she needs wou'd depart, though Jockey he lov'd his Moggy at heart; Jockey he wondred at Moggies strange huff, but Moggy was jealous, and that was enough. Tune of, You London lads be merry; or, Woo't thou be wilfull still my Joe.
publicationStmtPublisher: Printed for J. Deacon, atthe [sic] Angel in Guiltspur-street,
